Dear friends,

My best greetings from a wintery Stockholm. I hope this finds you all well =
and healthy, and that you have had good weeks since many of us last met! I =
realize it has already been a few weeks since we left our last meeting, and=
 I apologize for not being in touch sooner!

First and foremost, a big thanks to all of you who were part of the last me=
eting. The meeting of course was not without its challenges, but I am still=
 very glad that we could meet in the way that we did, for the discussions s=
hared, and for the plans made. Thank you!

As the year is now quickly coming to an end, I am writing to share some wor=
ds of thanks, some updates about 2025 and some specific questions following=
 our last meeting, connected to a shared newsletter

Thank you

You have heard me say this many times this year, and I will do it again: th=
ank you! It has been a challenging year in a lot of ways, big and small, an=
d some of those challenges has meant uncertainties for the future of our sh=
ared work. It has required patience and a lot of flexibility from all of yo=
u and I very much appreciate how you have all showed this during the year! =
Again, thank you!

2025

As we look ahead to 2025, we do it with a lot more clarity and certainty th=
an we have had in this last year. We know that a fourth cohort will start t=
heir journey with us shortly, we know that there will be various shared pro=
jects and initiatives going forward, and thanks to the work we did together=
 in our meeting, we also have good ideas about how we best use the network =
going forward. I will elaborate on one of these forward actions below =96 t=
he idea of a monthly newsletter - and then I will be in touch about other a=
ctivities and actions in the coming weeks. The aim is that at the time of o=
ur next regular online meeting, which will take place towards the end of Ja=
nuary, we will have a presentation of what the whole year of 2025 will enta=
il for the network.

Newsletter

During our last meeting, one of the ideas discussed was to begin producing =
a monthly newsletter. A big thanks to Ghaylen, Cheima and Abdi for capturin=
g this idea and summarizing it in writing! Please read through the next par=
t and answer the questions at the bottom.

The idea of the newsletter was that it will be issued once a month, focused=
 on the following topics:


  1.  The State of Human Rights: An overview of the general situation regar=
ding human rights in the region.



  1.  Existing Violations in Each Area: A detailed look at human rights vio=
lations specific to each subregion.



  1.  Latest Developments in Each Country Represented by Network Members: U=
pdates on human rights events and progress in countries where network membe=
rs are active.



  1.  Raising Awareness in the Field of Human Rights: Topics include digita=
l protection, physical protection, and the definition of key concepts.


Initially, this will start as an internal newsletter for activists within t=
he network. Once sustainability and commitment are confirmed, the project c=
an be expanded to include policy briefs aimed at human rights organizations=
 and decision-makers

For next steps, the following has been proposed:


  1.  Drafting a Code of Conduct
  2.  Establishing a framework to guide the process.
  3.  Preparing the Technical Aspects of the Newsletter:
  4.  Ensuring all necessary resources and tools are in place.
  5.  Appointing a Coordinator for Each Country
     *   Each country will have a representative from the network members.
  6.  Rotating Responsibility for Writing Each Month:
     *   Every month, one network member will take charge of authoring the =
content.


In terms of taking this forward, please get back to me with the following:


  1.  Are you interested in receiving should a monthly newsletter?



  1.  Are you interested and willing to be the coordinator for your country=
?



  1.  Are you interested and willing to be part of the rotating responsibil=
ity of writing each month?



Again, I will be in touch with more updates and questions about the next ye=
ar in the coming weeks. In the meantime, I wish you all a restful time as t=
he year comes to an end, a happy new year, and a good start to 2025!

My very best,
Erik




